---

FILES INCLUDED:

main.cpp
Contains the main function. Reads the command-line argument, generates the random cylinder request sequence, and runs each disk scheduling algorithm.

algorithms.cpp
Contains the implementations of the disk arm scheduling algorithms.

algorithms.h
Header file containing the function prototypes for the scheduling algorithms.

Makefile
Compiles the project and creates the executable named simarm.

README
Project description and operating instructions.

---

COMPILATION:

To compile the project:

make

---

RUNNING THE PROGRAM:

To execute the simulation:

./simarm <sequence_length>

Example:

./simarm 64

This generates a random sequence of 64 cylinder requests ranging from 0 to 999 and executes each disk arm scheduling algorithm using the same sequence.

---

CLEANING FILES:

To remove object files and the executable:

make clean

---

PROGRAM DESCRIPTION:

This program simulates disk arm scheduling by generating a random sequence of cylinder requests and executing three scheduling algorithms using the same request sequence.

The program:

* Accepts the sequence length as a command-line argument.
* Generates random cylinder requests between 0 and 999.
* Executes the First-Come, First-Served (FCFS) algorithm.
* Executes the Shortest Seek Time First (SSTF) algorithm.
* Executes the Elevator (SCAN) algorithm.
* Calculates and displays the total cylinder distance traveled by the disk arm for each algorithm.

---

DESIGN DECISIONS:

* The program is divided into multiple source files to keep the project organized.
* main.cpp acts as a table of contents and controls the simulation.
* algorithms.cpp contains the scheduling algorithms.
* algorithms.h stores the function prototypes.
* The same randomly generated sequence is used for all algorithms to ensure a fair comparison.
* Cylinder requests are generated within the range 0-999 as specified by the assignment.
* The simulation assumes the disk arm begins at cylinder 0.
* The Elevator algorithm initially moves upward through the request sequence.

